se.cbb.jprime.mcmc

Class Iteration

  • java.lang.Object
    • se.cbb.jprime.mcmc.Iteration
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Sampleable, InfoProvider

    public class Iteration
extends java.lang.Object
implements Sampleable, InfoProvider
    Holds the current and total number of iterations k for e.g. an MCMC chain. Iterations typically range between 0 and k, where 0 refers to a starting iteration (which is not counted, but may very well be sampled). Other objects may subscribe as listeners to increments of this object.
    Author:
    Joel Sj√∂strand.

      • increment

        public boolean increment()
        Increments the current iteration. If this exceeds the total number of iterations, nothing happens and false is returned. Listeners are notified synchronously before a call is returned.
        Returns:
        true if total number not reached before incrementing; false if total number reached before incrementing.
